source: crates/tokenless-cli/tests/e2e_tests.rs
description: secure-default global flag should be accepted
expression: output
---
LLM token optimization via schema and response compression

Usage: tokenless [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  compress-schema    Compress `OpenAI` `Function Calling` tool schemas
  compress-response  Compress a JSON API response (drop debug fields, truncate strings)
  compress-auto      Auto-detect the best compression strategy and apply it
  compress-toon      Encode JSON as TOON format
  decompress-toon    Decode TOON format back to JSON
  stats              View and manage compression statistics
  rewrite            Rewrite a shell command to its RTK equivalent (dry-run)
  hook               Agent hook protocol handlers (stdin JSON → stdout JSON)
  init               Install tokenless hooks for supported AI coding agents
  env-check          Check tool environment readiness
  mcp                Start MCP JSON-RPC 2.0 server on stdin/stdout
  demo               Show a demo of all compression strategies
  doctor             Run environment diagnostic (binary, PATH, hooks, stats)
  status             Show lightweight hook/stats status for quick daily check
  tui                Launch the interactive TUI dashboard
  help               Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --secure-default  Enable stricter secure defaults for validation, logging, and helper execution
  -h, --help            Print help
  -V, --version         Print version
